## Ansible syntaxes:

# ansible-playbook real-playbook.yml --syntax-check   // It will check the playbook does it have any syntax error.
# ansible-playbook real-playbook.yml --extra-vars "version=1.1"   // If you wanna override the variable value that you passed in playbook, use --extra-vars argument while executing ansible playbook.

# ansible-playbook variables.yml --syntax-check           // syntax checking
# ansible-playbook variables.yml --extra-vars "name=JOE"  // single variable value replace on the fly
# ansible-playbook variables.yml --extra-vars "name=JOE country=USA" // multiple variables value replacement on the fly using extra-vars

